Hartford Financial Services Group
Inc., the insurer that has been exiting life businesses to focus
on property-casualty coverage, said Virginia P. Ruesterholz has
been elected to the board of directors.  Ruesterholz, 52, was previously an executive vice president
at Verizon Communications Inc., according to a Business Wire
statement today from Hartford, which is based in the Connecticut
city of the same name.  To contact the reporter on this story:
